Sure! Here’s a simple test code for the ESP32 that blinks an LED connected to GPIO 2:

```cpp
void setup() {
  pinMode(2, OUTPUT); // Initialize GPIO 2 as an output
}

void loop() {
  digitalWrite(2, HIGH); // Turn the LED on
  delay(1000);           // Wait for a second
  digitalWrite(2, LOW);  // Turn the LED off
  delay(1000);           // Wait for a second
}
```

You can upload this code using the Arduino IDE. Let me know if you need more details or explanations!
